{"type":"message","id":"369ba1a9","parentId":"60958af2","timestamp":"2026-03-26T14:28:33.531Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_v3g9nUTGEavIAnWlL6vakGtb|fc_0a7381f2013991140169c54291d1f48191bf55d9a67b6ef37a","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"OpenClaw telegram audio transcription support voice notes docs\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1196,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4404758eca013785\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAudio and Voice Notes - OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4404758eca013785\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/nodes/audio\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"28580a6d0bae18b8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>The transcript is used for mention detection so voice notes can pass the mention gate</strong>. Fallback behavior: If transcription fails during preflight (timeout, API error, etc.), the message is processed based on text-only mention detection.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"28580a6d0bae18b8\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.openclaw.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0cd141e1e6cb5438\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAdd voice to OpenClaw with TTS STT and Talk Mode - LumaDock\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0cd141e1e6cb5438\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://lumadock.com/tutorials/openclaw-voice-tts-stt-talk-mode\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bac6f84f504b1d27\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTelegram treats them differently in the UI. By default OpenClaw sends TTS output as an audio file. If you want the round “voice note” bubble instead, <strong>the reply text must include the [[audio_as_voice]] directive</strong>.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bac6f84f504b1d27\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"lumadock.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d1955b063c27e987\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAudio and Voice Notes | Docs | OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d1955b063c27e987\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://openclaws.io/docs/nodes/audio\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2914831f7a1ace37\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>The transcript is used for mention detection so voice notes can pass the mention gate</strong>. ... If transcription fails during preflight (timeout, API error, etc.), the message is processed based on text-only mention detection.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2914831f7a1ace37\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"openclaws.io\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9493c2751e95fdef\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAudio and Voice Notes – OpenClaw - Open Source AI Coding Assistant\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9493c2751e95fdef\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://openclawlab.com/en/docs/nodes/audio/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"59cba426fb1fc294\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIf transcription fails during preflight (timeout, API error, etc.), the message is processed based on text-only mention detection. This ensures that mixed messages (text + audio) are never incorrectly dropped. Example: A user sends a voice note saying “Hey @Claude, what’s the weather?” in a Telegram group with requireMention: true.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"59cba426fb1fc294\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"openclawlab.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"eaf98ba48e5ad8cf\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Feature]: Automatic Voice Note Transcription · Issue #14374 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"eaf98ba48e5ad8cf\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/14374\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cc3cf811fc1d71c1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nManual transcription commands – Current workaround where the agent manually calls Whisper API via curl for each voice note. This defeats the purpose of seamless voice interaction. External webhook preprocessing – Set up a separate service to intercept Telegram webhooks, transcribe audio, and forward modified messages to OpenClaw.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cc3cf811fc1d71c1\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 12, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"OpenClaw telegram audio transcription support voice notes docs","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":1196,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4404758eca013785\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAudio and Voice Notes - OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4404758eca013785\">>>","url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/nodes/audio","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"28580a6d0bae18b8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n<strong>The transcript is used for mention detection so voice notes can pass the mention gate</strong>. Fallback behavior: If transcription fails during preflight (timeout, API error, etc.), the message is processed based on text-only mention detection.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"28580a6d0bae18b8\">>>","siteName":"docs.openclaw.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0cd141e1e6cb5438\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAdd voice to OpenClaw with TTS STT and Talk Mode - LumaDock\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0cd141e1e6cb5438\">>>","url":"https://lumadock.com/tutorials/openclaw-voice-tts-stt-talk-mode","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bac6f84f504b1d27\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTelegram treats them differently in the UI. By default OpenClaw sends TTS output as an audio file. If you want the round “voice note” bubble instead, <strong>the reply text must include the [[audio_as_voice]] directive</strong>.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bac6f84f504b1d27\">>>","siteName":"lumadock.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d1955b063c27e987\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAudio and Voice Notes | Docs | OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d1955b063c27e987\">>>","url":"https://openclaws.io/docs/nodes/audio","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2914831f7a1ace37\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n<strong>The transcript is used for mention detection so voice notes can pass the mention gate</strong>. ... If transcription fails during preflight (timeout, API error, etc.), the message is processed based on text-only mention detection.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2914831f7a1ace37\">>>","siteName":"openclaws.io"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9493c2751e95fdef\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAudio and Voice Notes – OpenClaw - Open Source AI Coding Assistant\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9493c2751e95fdef\">>>","url":"https://openclawlab.com/en/docs/nodes/audio/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"59cba426fb1fc294\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nIf transcription fails during preflight (timeout, API error, etc.), the message is processed based on text-only mention detection. This ensures that mixed messages (text + audio) are never incorrectly dropped. Example: A user sends a voice note saying “Hey @Claude, what’s the weather?” in a Telegram group with requireMention: true.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"59cba426fb1fc294\">>>","published":"2 weeks ago","siteName":"openclawlab.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"eaf98ba48e5ad8cf\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n[Feature]: Automatic Voice Note Transcription · Issue #14374 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"eaf98ba48e5ad8cf\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/14374","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cc3cf811fc1d71c1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nManual transcription commands – Current workaround where the agent manually calls Whisper API via curl for each voice note. This defeats the purpose of seamless voice interaction. External webhook preprocessing – Set up a separate service to intercept Telegram webhooks, transcribe audio, and forward modified messages to OpenClaw.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cc3cf811fc1d71c1\">>>","published":"February 12, 2026","siteName":"github.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774535313527}}
{"type":"message","id":"c8e4e0ef","parentId":"369ba1a9","timestamp":"2026-03-26T14:28:37.723Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Need local docs first per instructions.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a7381f2013991140169c542942b808191bb84790eb10cbebc\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JtNdKpVOi1vvI9HlB9V6DnlB|fc_0a7381f2013991140169c5429756d08191afc6c7805a031195","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\nodes\\audio.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\nodes\\\\audio.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_PDrYhZwNaw9aEIXocisoSKNe|fc_0a7381f2013991140169c5429756dc81918b9f4364d86bf609","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\" -Recurse -File | Select-String -Pattern \"speech-to-text|transcription|voice note|audio\" | Select-Object -First 30 | ForEach-Object { $_.Path + ':' + $_.LineNumber + ' ' + $_.Line }"},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"Get-ChildItem \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\" -Recurse -File | Select-String -Pattern \\\"speech-to-text|transcription|voice note|audio\\\" | Select-Object -First 30 | ForEach-Object { $_.Path + ':' + $_.LineNumber + ' ' + $_.Line }\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":2708,"output":173,"cacheRead":29696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32577,"cost":{"input":0.006770000000000001,"output":0.002595,"cacheRead":0.007424,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.016789000000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774535313533,"responseId":"resp_0a7381f2013991140169c5429372d08191918c1f31aa82dbc9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee678de8","parentId":"c8e4e0ef","timestamp":"2026-03-26T14:28:37.759Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_JtNdKpVOi1vvI9HlB9V6DnlB|fc_0a7381f2013991140169c5429756d08191afc6c7805a031195","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"How inbound audio/voice notes are downloaded, transcribed, and injected into replies\"\nread_when:\n  - Changing audio transcription or media handling\ntitle: \"Audio and Voice Notes\"\n---\n\n# Audio / Voice Notes (2026-01-17)\n\n## What works\n\n- **Media understanding (audio)**: If audio understanding is enabled (or auto‑detected), OpenClaw:\n  1. Locates the first audio attachment (local path or URL) and downloads it if needed.\n  2. Enforces `maxBytes` before sending to each model entry.\n  3. Runs the first eligible model entry in order (provider or CLI).\n  4. If it fails or skips (size/timeout), it tries the next entry.\n  5. On success, it replaces `Body` with an `[Audio]` block and sets `{{Transcript}}`.\n- **Command parsing**: When transcription succeeds, `CommandBody`/`RawBody` are set to the transcript so slash commands still work.\n- **Verbose logging**: In `--verbose`, we log when transcription runs and when it replaces the body.\n\n## Auto-detection (default)\n\nIf you **don’t configure models** and `tools.media.audio.enabled` is **not** set to `false`,\nOpenClaw auto-detects in this order and stops at the first working option:\n\n1. **Local CLIs** (if installed)\n   - `sherpa-onnx-offline` (requires `SHERPA_ONNX_MODEL_DIR` with encoder/decoder/joiner/tokens)\n   - `whisper-cli` (from `whisper-cpp`; uses `WHISPER_CPP_MODEL` or the bundled tiny model)\n   - `whisper` (Python CLI; downloads models automatically)\n2. **Gemini CLI** (`gemini`) using `read_many_files`\n3. **Provider keys** (OpenAI → Groq → Deepgram → Google)\n\nTo disable auto-detection, set `tools.media.audio.enabled: false`.\nTo customize, set `tools.media.audio.models`.\nNote: Binary detection is best-effort across macOS/Linux/Windows; ensure the CLI is on `PATH` (we expand `~`), or set an explicit CLI model with a full command path.\n\n## Config examples\n\n### Provider + CLI fallback (OpenAI + Whisper CLI)\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    media: {\n      audio: {\n        enabled: true,\n        maxBytes: 20971520,\n        models: [\n          { provider: \"openai\", model: \"gpt-4o-mini-transcribe\" },\n          {\n            type: \"cli\",\n            command: \"whisper\",\n            args: [\"--model\", \"base\", \"{{MediaPath}}\"],\n            timeoutSeconds: 45,\n          },\n        ],\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### Provider-only with scope gating\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    media: {\n      audio: {\n        enabled: true,\n        scope: {\n          default: \"allow\",\n          rules: [{ action: \"deny\", match: { chatType: \"group\" } }],\n        },\n        models: [{ provider: \"openai\", model: \"gpt-4o-mini-transcribe\" }],\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### Provider-only (Deepgram)\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    media: {\n      audio: {\n        enabled: true,\n        models: [{ provider: \"deepgram\", model: \"nova-3\" }],\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### Provider-only (Mistral Voxtral)\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    media: {\n      audio: {\n        enabled: true,\n        models: [{ provider: \"mistral\", model: \"voxtral-mini-latest\" }],\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### Echo transcript to chat (opt-in)\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    media: {\n      audio: {\n        enabled: true,\n        echoTranscript: true, // default is false\n        echoFormat: '📝 \"{transcript}\"', // optional, supports {transcript}\n        models: [{ provider: \"openai\", model: \"gpt-4o-mini-transcribe\" }],\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n## Notes & limits\n\n- Provider auth follows the standard model auth order (auth profiles, env vars, `models.providers.*.apiKey`).\n- Deepgram picks up `DEEPGRAM_API_KEY` when `provider: \"deepgram\"` is used.\n- Deepgram setup details: [Deepgram (audio transcription)](/providers/deepgram).\n- Mistral setup details: [Mistral](/providers/mistral).\n- Audio providers can override `baseUrl`, `headers`, and `providerOptions` via `tools.media.audio`.\n- Default size cap is 20MB (`tools.media.audio.maxBytes`). Oversize audio is skipped for that model and the next entry is tried.\n- Tiny/empty audio files below 1024 bytes are skipped before provider/CLI transcription.\n- Default `maxChars` for audio is **unset** (full transcript). Set `tools.media.audio.maxChars` or per-entry `maxChars` to trim output.\n- OpenAI auto default is `gpt-4o-mini-transcribe`; set `model: \"gpt-4o-transcribe\"` for higher accuracy.\n- Use `tools.media.audio.attachments` to process multiple voice notes (`mode: \"all\"` + `maxAttachments`).\n- Transcript is available to templates as `{{Transcript}}`.\n- `tools.media.audio.echoTranscript` is off by default; enable it to send transcript confirmation back to the originating chat before agent processing.\n- `tools.media.audio.echoFormat` customizes the echo text (placeholder: `{transcript}`).\n- CLI stdout is capped (5MB); keep CLI output concise.\n\n### Proxy environment support\n\nProvider-based audio transcription honors standard outbound proxy env vars:\n\n- `HTTPS_PROXY`\n- `HTTP_PROXY`\n- `https_proxy`\n- `http_proxy`\n\nIf no proxy env vars are set, direct egress is used. If proxy config is malformed, OpenClaw logs a warning and falls back to direct fetch.\n\n## Mention Detection in Groups\n\nWhen `requireMention: true` is set for a group chat, OpenClaw now transcribes audio **before** checking for mentions. This allows voice notes to be processed even when they contain mentions.\n\n**How it works:**\n\n1. If a voice message has no text body and the group requires mentions, OpenClaw performs a \"preflight\" transcription.\n2. The transcript is checked for mention patterns (e.g., `@BotName`, emoji triggers).\n3. If a mention is found, the message proceeds through the full reply pipeline.\n4. The transcript is used for mention detection so voice notes can pass the mention gate.\n\n**Fallback behavior:**\n\n- If transcription fails during preflight (timeout, API error, etc.), the message is processed based on text-only mention detection.\n- This ensures that mixed messages (text + audio) are never incorrectly dropped.\n\n**Opt-out per Telegram group/topic:**\n\n- Set `channels.telegram.groups.<chatId>.disableAudioPreflight: true` to skip preflight transcript mention checks for that group.\n- Set `channels.telegram.groups.<chatId>.topics.<threadId>.disableAudioPreflight` to override per-topic (`true` to skip, `false` to force-enable).\n- Default is `false` (preflight enabled when mention-gated conditions match).\n\n**Example:** A user sends a voice note saying \"Hey @Claude, what's the weather?\" in a Telegram group with `requireMention: true`. The voice note is transcribed, the mention is detected, and the agent replies.\n\n## Gotchas\n\n- Scope rules use first-match wins. `chatType` is normalized to `direct`, `group`, or `room`.\n- Ensure your CLI exits 0 and prints plain text; JSON needs to be massaged via `jq -r .text`.\n- For `parakeet-mlx`, if you pass `--output-dir`, OpenClaw reads `<output-dir>/<media-basename>.txt` when `--output-format` is `txt` (or omitted); non-`txt` output formats fall back to stdout parsing.\n- Keep timeouts reasonable (`timeoutSeconds`, default 60s) to avoid blocking the reply queue.\n- Preflight transcription only processes the **first** audio attachment for mention detection. Additional audio is processed during the main media understanding phase.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774535317758}}
{"type":"message","id":"043417c0","parentId":"ee678de8","timestamp":"2026-03-26T14:28:38.946Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_PDrYhZwNaw9aEIXocisoSKNe|fc_0a7381f2013991140169c5429756dc81918b9f4364d86bf609","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:300       \"source\": \"/audio\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:301       \"destination\": \"/nodes/audio\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:1341                   \"nodes/audio\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:1776                   \"zh-CN/nodes/audio\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\index.md:86     Send and receive images, audio, and documents.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\pi.md:444 const { text: cleanedText, mediaUrls, audioAsVoice, replyToId } = consumeReplyDirectives(chunk);\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:12 OpenClaw can convert outbound replies into audio using ElevenLabs, Microsoft, or OpenAI.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:13 It works anywhere OpenClaw can send audio.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:52 - [OpenAI Audio API reference](https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference/audio)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:56 - [Microsoft Speech output formats](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/ai-services/speech-service/rest-text-to-speech#audio-outputs)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:135         outputFormat: \"audio-24khz-48kbitrate-mono-mp3\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:173 ### Only reply with audio after an inbound voice message\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:206   - `inbound` only sends audio after an inbound voice message.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:207   - `tagged` only sends audio when the reply includes `[[tts]]` tags.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:218 - `maxTextLength`: hard cap for TTS input (chars). `/tts audio` fails if exceeded.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:236 - `microsoft.outputFormat`: Microsoft output format (e.g. `audio-24khz-48kbitrate-mono-mp3`).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:239 - `microsoft.saveSubtitles`: write JSON subtitles alongside the audio file.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:247 When `messages.tts.auto` is `tagged`, these directives are required to trigger audio.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:252 the audio.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:326 - **Microsoft**: uses `microsoft.outputFormat` (default `audio-24khz-48kbitrate-mono-mp3`).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:342 - attaches the generated audio to the reply.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:345 summary model), audio\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:356                    no  -> TTS -> attach audio\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:360                                       -> TTS -> attach audio\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:380 /tts audio Hello from OpenClaw\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:389 - `/tts audio` generates a one-off audio reply (does not toggle TTS on).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:393 The `tts` tool converts text to speech and returns an audio attachment for\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:395 the audio is delivered as a voice message rather than a file attachment.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\hooks.md:345 - **`message:received`**: When an inbound message is received from any channel. Fires early in processing before media understanding. Content may contain raw placeholders like `<media:audio>` for media attachments that haven't been processed yet.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\hooks.md:346 - **`message:transcribed`**: When a message has been fully processed, including audio transcription and link understanding. At this point, `transcript` contains the full transcript text for audio messages. Use this hook when you need access to transcribed audio content."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1203,"aggregated":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:300       \"source\": \"/audio\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:301       \"destination\": \"/nodes/audio\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:1341                   \"nodes/audio\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:1776                   \"zh-CN/nodes/audio\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\index.md:86     Send and receive images, audio, and documents.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\pi.md:444 const { text: cleanedText, mediaUrls, audioAsVoice, replyToId } = consumeReplyDirectives(chunk);\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:12 OpenClaw can convert outbound replies into audio using ElevenLabs, Microsoft, or OpenAI.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:13 It works anywhere OpenClaw can send audio.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:52 - [OpenAI Audio API reference](https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference/audio)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:56 - [Microsoft Speech output formats](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/ai-services/speech-service/rest-text-to-speech#audio-outputs)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:135         outputFormat: \"audio-24khz-48kbitrate-mono-mp3\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:173 ### Only reply with audio after an inbound voice message\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:206   - `inbound` only sends audio after an inbound voice message.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:207   - `tagged` only sends audio when the reply includes `[[tts]]` tags.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:218 - `maxTextLength`: hard cap for TTS input (chars). `/tts audio` fails if exceeded.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:236 - `microsoft.outputFormat`: Microsoft output format (e.g. `audio-24khz-48kbitrate-mono-mp3`).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:239 - `microsoft.saveSubtitles`: write JSON subtitles alongside the audio file.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:247 When `messages.tts.auto` is `tagged`, these directives are required to trigger audio.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:252 the audio.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:326 - **Microsoft**: uses `microsoft.outputFormat` (default `audio-24khz-48kbitrate-mono-mp3`).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:342 - attaches the generated audio to the reply.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:345 summary model), audio\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:356                    no  -> TTS -> attach audio\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:360                                       -> TTS -> attach audio\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:380 /tts audio Hello from OpenClaw\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:389 - `/tts audio` generates a one-off audio reply (does not toggle TTS on).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:393 The `tts` tool converts text to speech and returns an audio attachment for\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:395 the audio is delivered as a voice message rather than a file attachment.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\hooks.md:345 - **`message:received`**: When an inbound message is received from any channel. Fires early in processing before media understanding. Content may contain raw placeholders like `<media:audio>` for media attachments that haven't been processed yet.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\hooks.md:346 - **`message:transcribed`**: When a message has been fully processed, including audio transcription and link understanding. At this point, `transcript` contains the full transcript text for audio messages. Use this hook when you need access to transcribed audio content.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774535318944}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd0503ad","parentId":"043417c0","timestamp":"2026-03-26T14:28:56.341Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Need answer with research and config instructions, no actual key handling yet.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a7381f2013991140169c5429d18448191b7a3ba3bb17c8a18\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sim — dá para fazer, e sim: **Groq é uma opção boa e barata** para isso.\n\n**O que descobri:**\n- O OpenClaw **já suporta transcrição de áudio inbound nativamente**\n- A ordem de autodetecção inclui **providers com key**, e a doc local diz explicitamente: **OpenAI → Groq → Deepgram → Google** como opções de provider para áudio\n- Ou seja: não precisamos inventar gambiarra com bot externo ou scripts no Telegram. Dá para configurar no próprio OpenClaw\n\n**Como o OpenClaw faz isso:**\nQuando chega um áudio/voice note:\n1. baixa o ficheiro\n2. transcreve\n3. injecta a transcrição no corpo da mensagem\n4. eu passo a “ouvir” o teu áudio como texto\n\n---\n\n## Recomendação prática\n\nEu recomendo começar com **Groq** porque:\n- costuma ser **rápido**\n- costuma ser **barato**\n- serve bem para voice notes do Telegram\n\nPelo que encontrei, o modelo relevante é da família **Whisper Large v3** / **Whisper Large v3 Turbo** no Groq.  \nA referência externa que encontrei aponta custo por volta de **$0.111/hora de áudio** para Whisper Large v3, mas eu trataria esse número como **aproximado até confirmarmos na consola oficial do Groq**.\n\n---\n\n## Como configurar no OpenClaw\n\nA doc local do OpenClaw mostra que a config fica em:\n\n```json\ntools.media.audio\n```\n\nExemplo de configuração provider-only:\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    media: {\n      audio: {\n        enabled: true,\n        models: [\n          { provider: \"groq\", model: \"whisper-large-v3-turbo\" }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSe quisermos algo mais conservador, também dá para pôr fallback depois:\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    media: {\n      audio: {\n        enabled: true,\n        maxBytes: 20971520,\n        models: [\n          { provider: \"groq\", model: \"whisper-large-v3-turbo\" },\n          { provider: \"openai\", model: \"gpt-4o-mini-transcribe\" }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## O que ainda precisamos confirmar\n\nAntes de eu mexer:\n1. **qual modelo exacto do Groq** queres usar  \n   - eu começaria com `whisper-large-v3-turbo`\n2. **como o OpenClaw espera a auth do Groq nesta build**\n   - muito provavelmente por API key via config/env\n   - quero validar isso antes de te mandar colar a key\n\n---\n\n## Melhor próximo passo\n\nSe quiseres, eu faço agora a parte final:\n- confirmo na doc/config local **o formato exacto para auth do Groq**\n- preparo a alteração no `openclaw.json`\n- e depois tu só me mandas a API key para eu ligar isso e testar com um áudio teu\n\nSe quiser, já sigo nisso agora.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a7381f2013991140169c5429d77f88191b7d29272dd449647\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3340,"output":686,"cacheRead":32384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36410,"cost":{"input":0.008350000000000002,"output":0.01029,"cacheRead":0.008095999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.026736000000000003}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774535318947,"responseId":"resp_0a7381f2013991140169c54298d6548191a113054264ffc56d"}}
