ocs.json:1761                   \"zh-CN/automation/cron-vs-heartbeat\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:1965                   \"zh-CN/cli/cron\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\pi.md:121 �   ��� cron-tool.ts\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\pi.md:250 3. **OpenClaw Tools**: messaging, browser, canvas, sessions, cron, gateway, etc.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\auth-monitoring.md:26 This works in cron/systemd and requires no extra scripts.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\auth-monitoring.md:36 - `scripts/auth-monitor.sh`: cron/systemd timer target; sends alerts (ntfy or phone).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\cron-jobs.md:2 summary: \"Cron jobs + wakeups for the Gateway scheduler\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\cron-jobs.md:6   - Deciding between heartbeat and cron for scheduled tasks\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\cron-jobs.md:7 title: \"Cron Jobs\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\cron-jobs.md:10 # Cron jobs (Gateway scheduler)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\cron-jobs.md:12 > **Cron vs Heartbeat?** See [Cron vs Heartbeat](/automation/cron-vs-heartbeat) for guidance on when to use each.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\cron-jobs.md:14 Cron is the Gateway's built-in scheduler. It persists jobs, wakes the agent at\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\cron-jobs.md:18 cron is the mechanism.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roa